      <item>
		<title> Videonautica</title>
		<link>http://bestof.metafilter.com/2016/09/Videonautica</link>
		<description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/14405058@N08/7012933717" title="Nam June Paik - Megatron Matrix by Ryan Somma, on Flickr"&gt;&lt;img src="//farm8.staticflickr.com/7115/7012933717_96623662a0.jpg" width="500" height="332" alt="Nam June Paik - Megatron Matrix" style="display:block;margin:auto;"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:smaller;display:block;color:#999;margin-top:5px;"&gt;Nam June Paik - Megatron Matrix by Ryan Somma (cc by)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;How did that bizarre avant garde &lt;a href="http://www.metafilter.com/162093/New-Years-Avant-Day"&gt;show&lt;/a&gt; get broadcast, anyway? Mefi's own Dean 358 worked with &lt;a href="http://www.metafilter.com/162093/New-Years-Avant-Day#6698297"&gt;pioneering video artist Nam June Paik&lt;/a&gt;, and explains how Paik's personal &lt;a href="http://www.metafilter.com/162093/New-Years-Avant-Day#6699028"&gt;charm and enthusiasm got the art made&lt;/a&gt; and on the air.  "...getting access to video equipment in the 1980s was a really big deal. Video edit suites took up lots of space and cost millions of dollars to build and operate. Getting access to a satellite...well, absolutely unthinkable."&lt;/p&gt;</description>
